"title": "7374: high places",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7374",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Natural heights were sometimes the sites of shrines devoted to the LORD. However, the term usually refers to the places where shrines were set up to foreign gods, especially shrines where the worship of the LORD was in rivalry with Jerusalem.</p>\n<h2>High places referring to mountainous areas</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:19\">HAB 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:13\">DEU 32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:33\">PSA 18:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:34\">2SA 22:34</a></p>\n<h2>High places express divine lordship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:13\">AMO 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:3\">MIC 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>High places referring to shrines to the LORD</h2>\n<h3>High places were the focus of worship before the building of Solomon's temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:2-1Kgs3:3\">1KI 3:2–3:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>High places associated with Samuel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:12\">1SA 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:13-1Sam9:14\">1SA 9:13–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:19\">1SA 9:19</a></p>\n<h3>Associated with other prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:5\">1SA 10:5</a></strong></p>\n<h2>High places referring to foreign shrines</h2>\n<h3>In Canaan before the conquest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:29\">DEU 33:29</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Among Israel's neighbours</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa15:2\">ISA 15:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:12\">ISA 16:12</a></p>\n<h2>Israelite use of high places condemned</h2>\n<h3>The building of shrines on high places</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:31\">1KI 12:31</a></strong></p>\n<h3>High places condemned by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:30\">LEV 26:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:52\">NUM 33:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2\">DEU 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>High places condemned by the prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:28-Ezek20:29\">EZK 20:28–20:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:3\">JER 17:3</a></p>\n<h2>High places associated with foreign gods</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:35\">JER 32:35</a> <em>Baal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:7\">1KI 11:7</a> <em>Chemosh and Molech</em></p>\n<h2>Worship at the high places</h2>\n<h3>High places regarded as unsatisfactory places to worship the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:12\">2CH 32:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:4\">2KI 18:4</a> <em>The presence of Asherah poles is evidence of a consort for the LORD, typical of Baal worship, but alien to the Biblical concept of God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:1\">2CH 31:1</a></p>\n<h3>Characteristics of worship at the high places</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:11\">2KI 17:11</a> <em>burning incense</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:20\">2KI 23:20</a> <em>the presence of priests</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:25\">2CH 28:25</a> <em>sacrifices</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:7\">EZK 43:7</a> <em>a site for the tombs of kings</em></p>\n<h2>Removal of the high places</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:30\">LEV 26:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:52\">NUM 33:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:3\">2CH 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:6\">2CH 17:6</a></p>\n<h3>Commended for the zeal shown</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:5\">2KI 23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:8\">2KI 23:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:15\">2KI 23:15</a></p>\n<h3>Used as a test</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:14\">1KI 15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:43\">1KI 22:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:2-2Kgs12:3\">2KI 12:2–12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:3-2Kgs14:4\">2KI 14:3–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:3-2Kgs15:4\">2KI 15:3–15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:34-2Kgs15:35\">2KI 15:34–15:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:32-2Chr20:33\">2CH 20:32–20:33</a></p>",
